      "slug": "in-the-mood-for-a-hangout-movie",
      "title": "In The Mood For A: Hangout Movie",
      "desc": "“Say, man, you got a joint?”\n\n“No, not on me, man”\n\n“It'd be a lot cooler if you did”\n\nFunnily enough, it was Quentin Tarantino who coined the sub-genre as ‘hangout films’. For those who don’t know how to classify a film in the ‘hangout’ sub-genre, it’s a movie where plot and camerawork you may admire but whose primary attraction is the characters. However it’s not the same as a character driven film like Taxi Driver. It’s characterised by a certain lightness of tone, and (perhaps most crucially) a languid, almost meandering pace. The familiarity bred by the hangout film is that of the dorm room, the small high school class, or indeed the film crew; it arises not through… more",
